@@ -0,0 +1,147 @@
+# Prompt Template System Refactoring Summary
+
+## Overview
+This refactoring removes the LangChain dependency from the LlamaIndex prompt template system and replaces it with a simplified, native implementation.
+
+## Key Changes
+
+### 1. New Template Module (`llama_index/prompts/templates.py`)
+Created a new, standalone template system with the following classes:
+
+- **`BasePromptTemplate`**: Abstract base class for all prompt templates
+- **`PromptTemplate`**: Simple string-based template using Python's `{variable}` placeholders
+- **`FormattedPrompt`**: Represents a formatted prompt (can be converted to string or messages)
+- **`BaseMessagePromptTemplate`**: Base class for message templates
+- **`SystemMessagePromptTemplate`**: Templates for system messages
+- **`HumanMessagePromptTemplate`**: Templates for user messages
+- **`AIMessagePromptTemplate`**: Templates for assistant messages
+- **`ChatPromptTemplate`**: Template for multi-message conversations
+
+**Key Features:**
+- Uses standard Python string formatting with regex-based variable extraction
+- No external dependencies beyond LlamaIndex's own `ChatMessage` classes
+- Clean, simple API that matches the LangChain interface for compatibility
+
+### 2. Updated Prompt Class (`llama_index/prompts/base.py`)
+Refactored the `Prompt` class to use the new template system:
+
+- Changed from wrapping LangChain prompts to wrapping our own `BasePromptTemplate`
+- Added backward compatibility for `langchain_prompt` and `langchain_prompt_selector` parameters
+- Updated all methods to use the new template interface:
+  - `format()` - formats template to string
+  - `format_messages()` - formats template to list of `ChatMessage` objects
+  - `get_prompt()` - gets the selected template (replaces `get_langchain_prompt()`)
+- Maintained all existing functionality (partial formatting, metadata, output parsers)
+
+### 3. Updated Prompt Selector (`llama_index/prompts/prompt_selector.py`)
+Simplified the `PromptSelector` class:
+
+- Removed LangChain `BasePromptTemplate` dependency
+- Now uses `Any` type for prompts (more flexible)
+- Added Pydantic config for `arbitrary_types_allowed`
+- Kept the same selection logic based on LLM characteristics
+
+### 4. Updated Chat Prompts (`llama_index/prompts/chat_prompts.py`)
+Changed imports to use the new template classes:
+
+- Replaced `from llama_index.bridge.langchain import ...` with `from llama_index.prompts.templates import ...`
+- Changed `from_langchain_prompt()` calls to `from_prompt()` calls
+- All chat prompt definitions remain functionally identical
+
+### 5. Updated Default Prompt Selectors (`llama_index/prompts/default_prompt_selectors.py`)
+Updated to use the new API:
+
+- Changed `get_langchain_prompt()` calls to `get_prompt()` calls
+- Changed `langchain_prompt_selector` parameter to `prompt_selector`
+- Maintained all existing selector functionality
+
+### 6. Updated LangChain Bridge (`llama_index/bridge/langchain.py`)
+Maintained backward compatibility while removing prompt template dependencies:
+
+- Added lazy imports for prompt template classes using `__getattr__`
+- Now imports prompt templates from `llama_index.prompts.templates` instead of LangChain
+- Prevents circular import issues by deferring template imports
+- All other LangChain imports remain unchanged (agents, tools, LLMs, embeddings, etc.)
+
+## API Changes
+
+### Breaking Changes
+**None!** All changes are backward compatible.
+
+### Deprecated (but still functional)
+- `Prompt.get_langchain_prompt()` - use `Prompt.get_prompt()` instead
+- `Prompt.from_langchain_prompt()` - use `Prompt.from_prompt()` instead
+- `Prompt(langchain_prompt=...)` - use `Prompt(prompt=...)` instead
+- `Prompt(langchain_prompt_selector=...)` - use `Prompt(prompt_selector=...)` instead
+
+### New API
+- `Prompt.get_prompt(llm)` - Get the template (selected based on LLM)
+- `Prompt.from_prompt(template)` - Create from a `BasePromptTemplate`
+- `Prompt.from_existing_prompt(prompt)` - Create from existing `Prompt` instance
+
+## Benefits
+
+1. **Reduced Dependencies**: No longer depends on LangChain for core prompt functionality
+2. **Simplified Code**: Cleaner, more maintainable implementation
+3. **Better Control**: Full control over prompt template behavior
+4. **Backward Compatible**: Existing code continues to work without changes
+5. **Performance**: Lighter weight without LangChain overhead for prompt operations
+6. **Flexibility**: Easier to extend and customize prompt behavior
+
+## Testing
+
+All existing tests pass:
+- ✅ `tests/indices/test_prompt_helper.py` (7 tests)
+- ✅ Basic prompt formatting
+- ✅ Partial formatting
+- ✅ Chat prompt messages
+- ✅ Prompt selectors
+- ✅ Template classes
+- ✅ Backward compatibility
+- ✅ Bridge imports
+- ✅ Input variable extraction
+- ✅ Refine prompts
+
+## Migration Guide
+
+### For Users
+**No changes required!** All existing code will continue to work.
+
+### For Contributors
+When creating new prompts, prefer the new API:
+
+```python
+# Old way (still works)
+from llama_index.bridge.langchain import PromptTemplate
+template = PromptTemplate.from_template("Hello {name}")
+
+# New way (preferred)
+from llama_index.prompts.templates import PromptTemplate
+template = PromptTemplate.from_template("Hello {name}")
+```
+
+## Files Modified
+
+1. `/testbed/llama_index/prompts/templates.py` - **NEW** - Core template implementation
+2. `/testbed/llama_index/prompts/base.py` - Refactored to use new templates
+3. `/testbed/llama_index/prompts/prompt_selector.py` - Removed LangChain dependency
+4. `/testbed/llama_index/prompts/chat_prompts.py` - Updated imports
+5. `/testbed/llama_index/prompts/default_prompt_selectors.py` - Updated API calls
+6. `/testbed/llama_index/bridge/langchain.py` - Added lazy imports for compatibility
+
+## Compatibility
+
+- ✅ Fully backward compatible with existing code
+- ✅ All prompt types work (simple, chat, refine, etc.)
+- ✅ Prompt selectors work with different LLM types
+- ✅ Partial formatting works
+- ✅ Metadata and output parsers work
+- ✅ Bridge imports work for compatibility
+
+## Future Improvements
+
+Potential future enhancements:
+1. Add more template validation
+2. Support for more complex template syntax (if needed)
+3. Performance optimizations for template parsing
+4. Additional template types for specialized use cases
